Clinically significant drug or alcohol abuse within the preceding six months;
Significant neurologic, psychiatric, endocrine, metabolic, immunologic, cardiovascular, pulmonary, or hepatic disorder within the preceding six months judged to impair participation;
Presence of central nervous system involvement of multiple myeloma.

History of uncontrolled intercurrent illness limiting protocol compliance;
Active infection requiring systemic therapy;
Concurrent participation in another investigational drug or device study;
Impaired gastrointestinal function or disease altering oral drug absorption;
Known or suspected active or untreated central nervous system metastases causing neurologic symptoms;
Current active liver disease of any etiology;
HIV-positive status (unless strict virologic/immunologic criteria are met);
Clinically relevant cardiovascular disease;
Past or present active interstitial lung disease;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Inability or unwillingness to comply with scheduled visits, study treatment, labs, or procedures;
Any other medically significant illness, condition, surgery, lab abnormality, or circumstance deemed by the investigator to jeopardize patient safety or compromise evaluation of study outcomes.

