Has breast cancer amenable to curative‑intent treatment;
Early recurrence occurring fewer than six months after completion of adjuvant or neoadjuvant chemotherapy;
Symptomatic visceral crisis posing imminent threat to life;
Active autoimmune disease requiring systemic therapy within the preceding two years;
History of non‑infectious pneumonitis or interstitial lung disease requiring corticosteroids, or currently active pneumonitis/interstitial lung disease;
Active infection necessitating systemic antimicrobial therapy.

History of severe uncontrolled systemic bacterial, fungal, or viral infection requiring ongoing antimicrobial therapy;
Malignant hypertension (≥99th percentile BP plus 5 mmHg with retinal hemorrhage or cotton‑wool spots);
Life expectancy <3 months due to non‑HSCT‑TMA causes;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Receipt of any investigational agent or device within four weeks before enrollment;
Alanine transaminase or aspartate transaminase >5 times upper limit of normal within 28 days prior to consent;
Employment relationship with sponsor, CRO, investigators, or study personnel;
Known hypersensitivity to any component of the study drug;
Any medical condition judged by the investigator to increase undue risk.

history of pneumonitis or interstitial lung disease;
uncontrolled cardiac disease including symptomatic heart failure;
significant hepatic impairment (bilirubin >2× ULN or Child‑Pugh C);
severe renal dysfunction (creatinine clearance <30 mL/min);
active untreated central nervous system infections or meningitis;
known human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) infection or chronic hepatitis B/C infection;
untreated or unstable brain metastases;
pregnant or nursing women;
concomitant enrollment in another interventional clinical trial;
unable to tolerate study medications due to allergy or intolerance.

