History of active infection including untreated tuberculosis, human immunodeficiency virus, or chronic viral hepatitis;
Uncontrolled cardiovascular disease such as recent myocardial infarction, unstable angina, congestive heart failure NYHA Class III/IV;
Significant pulmonary comorbidity including ongoing grade > 2 interstitial lung disease or pneumonitis;
Severe hepatic impairment (Child‑Pugh C) or bilirubin >​1.5 times upper limit of normal;
Renal insufficiency with creatinine clearance <30 mL/minute;
Active central nervous system involvement or uncontrolled brain metastasis;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding; unwillingness to use adequate contraception;
Concurrent malignancy requiring active therapy or known hypersensitivity to investigational product components;
Any condition judged by investigators to interfere with safety evaluation or protocol compliance.

History of active infection including untreated tuberculosis, human immunodeficiency virus, or chronic viral hepatitis;
Uncontrolled cardiovascular disease such as recent myocardial infarction, unstable angina, congestive heart failure NYHA Class III/IV;
Significant pulmonary comorbidity including ongoing grade > 2 interstitial lung disease or pneumonitis;
Severe hepatic impairment (Child‑Pugh C) or bilirubin >​1.5 times upper limit of normal;
Renal insufficiency with creatinine clearance <30 mL/minute;
Active central nervous system involvement or uncontrolled brain metastasis;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding; unwillingness to use adequate contraception;
Concurrent malignancy requiring active therapy or known hypersensitivity to investigational product components;
Any condition judged by investigators to interfere with safety evaluation or protocol compliance.

History of active infection including untreated tuberculosis, human immunodeficiency virus, or chronic viral hepatitis;
Uncontrolled cardiovascular disease such as recent myocardial infarction, unstable angina, congestive heart failure NYHA Class III/IV;
Significant pulmonary comorbidity including ongoing grade > 2 interstitial lung disease or pneumonitis;
Severe hepatic impairment (Child‑Pugh C) or bilirubin >​1.5 times upper limit of normal;
Renal insufficiency with creatinine clearance <30 mL/minute;
Active central nervous system involvement or uncontrolled brain metastasis;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding; unwillingness to use adequate contraception;
Concurrent malignancy requiring active therapy or known hypersensitivity to investigational product components;
Any condition judged by investigators to interfere with safety evaluation or protocol compliance.

Participants who cannot undergo magnetic resonance imaging;
Intraocular primary CNS lymphoma without accompanying brain or spinal cord disease;
History of grade ≥3 allergic or hypersensitivity reaction to pembrolizumab, high‑dose methotrexate, temozolomide, rituximab, or their excipients;
Active autoimmune disease requiring systemic immunosuppressive therapy within the past 2 years (excluding physiological replacements);
Live viral vaccination administered within 30 days preceding study entry (temporal washout excluded from space definition);
Known active hepatitis B infection (positive HBsAg) or active hepatitis C infection (detectable HCV RNA);
Confirmed active Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection;
Immunodeficiency conditions or chronic systemic glucocorticoid use exceeding 10 mg/day prednisolone equivalents;
Previous allogenic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation;
Large pleural effusions, significant ascites, or generalized edema;
Uncontrolled diabetes mellitus with glycated haemoglobin greater than 8 %;
Poorly controlled steroid‑induced diabetes mellitus with glycated haemoglobin greater than 8 %;
Recent (<30 day) live‑attenuated influenza nasal spray vaccination (other seasonal flu vaccines permitted);
Concurrent use of moderate or strong CYP3A4/5 inhibitors or inducers (required cessation before study initiation);
Use of enzyme‑inducing anticonvulsant drugs (must be replaced prior to enrolment);
Pregnancy, lactation, or intention to become pregnant or sire a child during the study period up to 120 days after the last dose;
Psychiatric illness or substance misuse deemed to compromise protocol compliance.

History of severe coagulopathy or contraindicated antiplatelet/anticoagulant agents (except low‑dose aspirin up to 100 mg/day or low‑molecular‑weight heparin);
Concurrent anticancer therapy for an active non‑myelofibrosis malignancy;
Uncontrolled comorbidities such as serious cardiac, respiratory, hepatic, or renal disease;
Active central nervous system involvement or untreated/uncontrolled brain lesions;
Known human immunodeficiency virus, chronic hepatitis B or C infections;
Pregnancy, breastfeeding, or unwillingness to use effective contraception;
Inability to comply with protocol procedures or follow‑up evaluations.

Inoperable locally advanced or metastatic breast cancer;
Pathological complete response after neoadjuvant therapy;
History of any other malignant disease except non‑melanoma skin cancer or cervical intraepithelial neoplasia, unless in complete remission off therapy for ≥5 years;
Severe or uncontrolled systemic illnesses deemed unsuitable by investigators;
Left ventricular ejection fraction < 50% with New York Heart Association Class II or higher heart failure;
Mean resting QTcF interval > 480 ms at screening;
Concurrent exogenous reproductive hormone therapy or non‑topical hormonal therapy for non‑cancer indications;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Known hypersensitivity to camizestrant, its excipients, or chemically similar compounds;
Hypersensitivity/intolerance to luteinizing hormone‑releasing hormone agonists in pre/perimenopausal females or males.

Pleural effusion, pericardial effusion, or ascites requiring recurrent drainage procedures;
history of noninfectious pneumonitis or interstitial lung disease requiring steroids or currently active pneumonitis/ILF;
clinically severe pulmonary compromise due to intercurrent illness;
active or historical immune deficiency (excluding well‑controlled HIV on ART);
significant cardiovascular disease within six months (coronary/peripheral artery surgery or angiography, myocardial infarction, symptomatic CHF NYHA II or higher, unstable arrhythmias);
arterial thrombotic event (stroke/TIA) within six months;
actively infectious conditions requiring systemic antimicrobial therapy;
previous allogenic stem cell or solid organ transplantation;
leptomeningeal carcinomatosis;
untreated or symptomatic central nervous system metastases;
unresolved acute infection or ongoing systemic steroid/immunosuppression (>10 mg prednisolone equivalents daily) within seven days;
additional malignant neoplasm that is progressive or requires active treatment within three years;
active hepatitis A, B, or C infection (unless virologically suppressed);
other uncontrolled or significant comorbidity as stipulated by protocol.

